On some terminals (notably VT100 compatibles), GNU grep with color enabled will
skip over writing the character at the right edge of the terminal if the search
string includes the text at that edge.

The workaround is to set the environment variable GREP_COLORS=ne

References:

https://unix.stackexchange.com/questions/283983/how-does-a-program-decide-whether-or-not-to-have-coloured-output/284000#284000

https://invisible-island.net/xterm/xterm.faq.html#grep_colors
